<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<!--
    HSK material conversion for VRE Waster.

    VRE_BurnBarrel — small primitive metal incinerator (1x1).

    HSK pattern: switch from fixed Steel to stuffCategories RuggedMetallic +
    costStuffCount (HSK convention for outdoor / weather-exposed metal
    fixtures), and add a single ComponentIndustrial for the fab work that
    goes into a sealed combustion barrel.

    Reference: HSK WastepackAtomizer (the closest pollution-themed building)
    uses RuggedMetallic + 200 stuff + 4 CompInd + 2 ElecComp + AdvMech +
    NanostructuringChip. That's a high-tech waste-cleaning device — the
    burn barrel is a *primitive* trash can you set on fire, so it sits at
    the bottom of the tier with just the bare metal-fab cost.

    No other Waster content needs HSK or CE patching. The 17 pollution-themed
    genes (ToxAbsorption, PollutionRage, PollutionRegeneration, etc.) and
    11 pollution stimulus hediffs are pure stat-based mechanics with no
    tools, verbs, armor offsets, weapons, or apparel.
-->
<Patch>

    <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
        <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[defName="VRE_BurnBarrel"]/costList</xpath>
        <value>
            <stuffCategories>
                <li>RuggedMetallic</li>
            </stuffCategories>
            <costStuffCount>45</costStuffCount>
            <costList>
                <ComponentIndustrial>1</ComponentIndustrial>
            </costList>
        </value>
    </Operation>

</Patch>
